The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Murali to stay in WI
                                                                                                                       7                                      Murali to stay in WI
                      
	Colombo: Injured spinner Muttiah Muralidharan is recovering slowly and will remain with the squad for the World Twenty20 in the Caribbean, Sri Lanka Cricket (SLC) stated on Wednesday.         
	Muralidharan, 38, who is also the teams vice-captain, has made significant progress and is recovering from a groin injury picked up during last Fridays opening game against New Zealand, which Sri Lanka lost by two wickets.         
	SLC on Monday said the off-spinner had been advised to rest for two or three weeks.         
	Murali has begun his running programme paving the way for some light bowling shortly, team physiotherapist Tommy Simsek said in a statement released by the SLC in Colombo. Murali is to remain in the West Indies after making significant progress. The team support staff are keeping a close eye on Muralis rate of improvement, Simsek said.         
	Sri Lanka will take on the West Indies in Bridgetown on Friday.           (AGENCIES)                                                                                                                 
